The paper proposes a statistical method for ability estimation in a personalized computer-aided question generation system. This involves capturing learning outcomes over time and providing a flexible measurement based on acquisition distributions. The paper also discusses the use of empirical data to validate the proposed method. Based on this, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, as the paper deals with statistical methods and machine learning techniques. The sub-category cs.CE (Computer Engineering) is also likely, as the paper discusses the development of a computer-aided testing environment. The sub-categories cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.EDU (Education) are also possible, as the paper discusses the use of natural language processing techniques and the application of the proposed method in an educational setting.
